---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ContactForm from '../../components/ContactForm.astro';
import RelatedServices from '../../components/RelatedServices.astro';
import ServiceAreasLink from '../../components/ServiceAreasLink.astro';
import { SITE_CONFIG } from '../../config';
import { generateServiceSchema } from '../../utils/schema';

const serviceSchema = generateServiceSchema('basement-flooring', 'Professional basement concrete floor installation and repair in Deptford, NJ. Durable basement flooring with free estimates.');
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Basement Concrete Floor Installation in Deptford, NJ"
  description="Basement concrete floor specialists in Deptford, NJ. New installation, repair, leveling, and moisture barrier services. Transform your basement with durable concrete flooring."
  schema={serviceSchema}
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Basement Concrete Floor Installation in Deptford, New Jersey</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">Professional basement floor installation and repair services. Transform your basement with durable concrete flooring.</p>
      <a href="#contact-form" class="cta-primary">Get Free Basement Floor Estimate</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Basement Flooring Services</h2>
      <p>We provide professional basement concrete floor installation and repair services for residential and commercial properties.</p>

      <h3>What's Included in Our Basement Flooring Service</h3>
      <p>When you choose Deptford Concrete Contractors for your basement flooring project, you receive comprehensive service:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Free Site Evaluation:</strong> We assess your basement, existing floor condition, moisture issues, and structural requirements at no cost</li>
        <li><strong>Floor Design:</strong> Custom floor design that addresses your specific needs, whether new installation or repair</li>
        <li><strong>Moisture Assessment:</strong> Evaluation of moisture levels and recommendations for moisture barriers if needed</li>
        <li><strong>Site Preparation:</strong> Proper preparation including removal of old flooring (if needed) and surface preparation</li>
        <li><strong>Moisture Barrier Installation:</strong> When required, proper vapor barrier installation to prevent moisture issues</li>
        <li><strong>Quality Materials:</strong> High-grade concrete mixes appropriate for interior basement use</li>
        <li><strong>Professional Installation:</strong> Expert installation by experienced concrete professionals</li>
        <li><strong>Leveling Services:</strong> Proper floor leveling to ensure a smooth, even surface</li>
        <li><strong>Finishing Options:</strong> Smooth finish or other options based on your intended use</li>
        <li><strong>Cleanup:</strong> Complete site cleanup after installation</li>
        <li><strong>Maintenance Guidance:</strong> Advice on proper care and maintenance for your basement floor</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Our Basement Floor Installation Process</h3>
      <p>We follow a detailed process to ensure your basement floor is installed correctly:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Site Evaluation:</strong> We assess your basement, including existing floor condition, moisture levels, and structural requirements</li>
        <li><strong>Moisture Testing:</strong> Evaluation of moisture levels to determine if vapor barriers are needed</li>
        <li><strong>Design & Planning:</strong> We create a floor plan that addresses your needs and any existing issues</li>
        <li><strong>Surface Preparation:</strong> Removal of old flooring (if needed) and proper surface preparation</li>
        <li><strong>Moisture Barrier Installation:</strong> Installation of vapor barrier when required to prevent moisture issues</li>
        <li><strong>Reinforcement (if needed):</strong> Placement of reinforcement for larger areas or specific requirements</li>
        <li><strong>Concrete Pouring:</strong> Placement of high-quality concrete mix appropriate for basement use</li>
        <li><strong>Leveling:</strong> Proper leveling to ensure a smooth, even surface</li>
        <li><strong>Finishing:</strong> Proper finishing based on your intended use</li>
        <li><strong>Curing:</strong> Proper curing time to ensure maximum strength and durability</li>
        <li><strong>Final Inspection:</strong> Quality check to ensure your floor meets all standards</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Common Issues Basement Flooring Solves</h3>
      <p>Our basement flooring services address many common basement problems:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Moisture Problems:</strong> Proper installation with moisture barriers prevents water damage and mold growth</li>
        <li><strong>Uneven Surfaces:</strong> Leveling services create smooth, even floors suitable for any use</li>
        <li><strong>Damaged Existing Floors:</strong> Repair or replacement of cracked, damaged, or deteriorating basement floors</li>
        <li><strong>Unusable Basement Space:</strong> Quality flooring transforms basements into usable living or storage space</li>
        <li><strong>Cold Floors:</strong> Proper concrete installation can help with temperature control in basements</li>
        <li><strong>Property Value:</strong> Quality basement flooring enhances property value and usability</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>What Happens When You Call</h3>
      <p>Getting your basement floor installed or repaired is straightforward with our streamlined process:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Initial Contact (24-48 Hour Response):</strong> When you reach out via phone or our contact form, we'll respond within 24-48 hours to schedule your free estimate</li>
        <li><strong>Free On-Site Estimate:</strong> We visit your property to assess your basement, evaluate moisture issues, and provide a detailed written estimate</li>
        <li><strong>Project Planning:</strong> Once you approve the estimate, we handle all planning including material ordering and scheduling</li>
        <li><strong>Professional Installation:</strong> Our experienced team completes your basement floor installation or repair efficiently and professionally</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Our Customer Service Promise</h3>
      <p>At Deptford Concrete Contractors, we believe in complete transparency and honest communication:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>No Hidden Fees:</strong> Your written estimate includes all costs - materials, labor, moisture barriers, and cleanup - no surprises</li>
        <li><strong>Clear Communication:</strong> We keep you informed at every step, from initial estimate through project completion</li>
        <li><strong>Realistic Timelines:</strong> We provide honest timelines based on project scope - typically 1-3 days for most basement floors</li>
        <li><strong>Quality Guarantee:</strong> We stand behind our work and ensure your basement floor meets all quality standards</li>
        <li><strong>Responsive Service:</strong> We respond to questions and concerns promptly, typically within 24-48 hours</li>
        <li><strong>Licensed & Insured:</strong> Full professional coverage protects you and your property throughout the project</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Basement Flooring Investment Factors</h3>
      <p>Understanding what affects your basement flooring investment helps you make informed decisions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Basement Size:</strong> Larger basements require more materials and labor</li>
        <li><strong>Existing Floor Condition:</strong> Removal of old flooring or extensive preparation affects cost</li>
        <li><strong>Moisture Issues:</strong> Properties with moisture problems may need vapor barriers or additional preparation</li>
        <li><strong>Leveling Requirements:</strong> Significant leveling work may require additional materials and time</li>
        <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> Difficult access to basement may require special equipment or additional time</li>
        <li><strong>Finishing Options:</strong> Special finishes or treatments can impact cost</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We provide free, detailed estimates that break down all costs so you understand exactly what you're investing in. There are no hidden fees or surprise charges - what we quote is what you pay.</p>

      <h3>Related Services</h3>
      <p>Basement flooring often pairs with other concrete services:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/services/concrete-slabs">Concrete Slabs</a> - Similar slab installation expertise</li>
        <li><a href="/services/driveways">Driveway Installation</a> - Complete your property's concrete surfaces</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Areas We Serve</h3>
      <p>We provide basement flooring services throughout <a href="/locations/deptford-nj">Deptford</a>, <a href="/locations/west-deptford-nj">West Deptford</a>, <a href="/locations/woodbury-nj">Woodbury</a>, <a href="/locations/glassboro-nj">Glassboro</a>, and <a href="/locations">all surrounding Gloucester County communities</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <RelatedServices currentService="basement-flooring" />
  <ServiceAreasLink serviceName="Basement Flooring" />

  <section id="contact-form" class="contact-section">
    <div class="container">
      <ContactForm 
        title="Get Your Free Basement Floor Estimate"
        service="basement-flooring"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Basement Flooring FAQs</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Do I need a moisture barrier under my basement floor?</h3>
          <p>Moisture barriers are often recommended for basement floors to prevent moisture issues. We'll assess your basement's moisture levels during the free estimate and recommend the appropriate solution.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How long does basement floor installation take?</h3>
          <p>Most basement floor installations take 1-3 days depending on size, preparation needs, and whether existing flooring needs to be removed. We'll provide a detailed timeline during your free estimate.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can you level an existing uneven basement floor?</h3>
          <p>Yes, we can level existing basement floors using self-leveling concrete or by installing a new floor over the existing one. We'll assess your situation during the free estimate and recommend the best approach.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Will a new basement floor help with moisture problems?</h3>
          <p>A properly installed basement floor with a vapor barrier can help reduce moisture issues, but it's important to address underlying moisture sources. We'll assess your situation and recommend the best solution.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can I install flooring over a new concrete basement floor?</h3>
          <p>Yes, once properly cured, a concrete basement floor can serve as a base for various flooring types. We'll ensure the surface is properly prepared for your intended use.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

